          '    1.1.  Identity Data. We may collect and store Personal Information that you provide to us when accessing or using the Services. “Personal Information” means information relating to a person who is or can be identified directly from that information. This includes your name, gender, date of birth, address, location, telephone number, mobile number, email address, payment details, payment card details or bank account details. Personal Information does not include: (1) aggregated or anonymized information; (2) information about you that is provided by third parties; or (3) information that is posted to publicly accessible areas of the Services. Examples of Personal Information we collect include information that you provide when you (a) create or update your account, (b) communicate with us, (c) contact us, (d) update your profile or post information using your Profile, we may also collect verification information.\n\n  1.2.  Profile Information. EZWAGE may also collect and store your profile information which may include your username, password, your interests, preferences, feedback and survey responses. \n\n  1.3.  Other Personal Data. We may also collect and store other Personal Data, which may include additional financial information such as household income, financial income other than salary and financial liabilities. \n\n  1.4.  Financial Information. EZWAGE can or may collect and store any Financial Information if you use/ access our Platforms. Financial Information refers to bank account details, debit card information, salary and statutory payments etc. (hereinafter, “Financial Information”). For a successful transaction, you will be asked to provide your Financial Information. EZWAGE can or may retain such information for future transactions.\n\n  1.5.  Banking and Transaction Details. EZWAGE can or may collect and store any Banking and transaction details. Banking details may include transaction history, transaction amounts and descriptions, 