          '    7.1. The User is aware that a ‘Cookie’ is a small piece of information stored by a web server on a web browser so it can later be traced back from that particular browser, and that cookies are useful for enabling the browser to remember information specific to a given user, including but not limited to a User’s login identification, password, etc. The User is aware that the Platforms places both permanent and temporary cookies in the User’s computer’s hard drive and web browser, and does hereby expressly consent to the same.\n\n  7.2.  The User is further aware that the Platforms use data collection devices such as cookies on certain pages of the Platforms to help analyze web page flow, measure promotional effectiveness, and promotes trust and safety, and that certain features of the Platforms are only available through the use of such cookies. While the User is free to decline the Platform’s cookies if the User’s browser permits, the User may consequently be unable to use certain features on the Platforms.\n\n  7.3.  Additionally, the User is aware that they might encounter cookies or other similar devices on certain pages of the Platform that are placed by third parties or affiliates of the Platform. The User expressly agrees and acknowledges that the Platforms does not control the use of such cookies/other devices by third parties, that the Platforms is in no way responsible for the same, and that the User assumes any and all risks in this regard.',
